  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally involves financial transactions designed to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Legal definitions typically include three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration - Reintroducing funds into the economy as seemingly legitimate income\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most criminal codes require:\n- Knowledge of funds' illegal origins\n- Intent to disguise source\n- Deliberate financial transactions to hide criminal proceeds\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
